sentences: Shani Diluka (born 7 November 1976 in Monaco) is a pianist of Sri Lankan parents.
Enrolled in the Conservatoire de Paris in 1997, she studied with Georges Pludermacher and François-Frédéric Guy and later with Marie-Françoise Bucquet, Nicholas Angelich and Bruno Rigutto.
Other encounters were to follow in 2005, when she joined the Fondation de Come, presided by Martha Argerich.
Pieces of C. P. E. Bach et W. A. Mozart performed on modern piano and on an copie of Walter 1790 thanks to the Fondation Royaumont.
(Mirare / Harmonia Mundi 2019)
(Mirare / Harmonia Mundi 2017)
(Mirare / Harmonia Mundi 2017)
Schubert - Des Fragments aux étoiles 12 Ländler D790, Hungarian Melody, Sonata in B flat major D960 of Franz Schubert (Mirare / Harmonia Mundi 2016)

Babar et le Père Noël (livre-CD) Natalie Dessay, accompanied by the pianist Shani Diluka, tells the story of Babar and Father Christmas with pieces of C. Saint-Saëns, E. Satie, C. Debussy, M. Ravel, G. Bizet and, of course, F. Poulenc with the original text of Jean de Brunhoff.
